<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-23T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="521" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/7941: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-23T11:00:00-05:00">February 23, 1934—11
                                    a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>14. Your 61, February 22, 8 p.m. You may in your discretion say orally to
                            Somoza that there has been no change in the Department’s policy. We,
                            however, believe it inadvisable to make any public statement either in
                            Managua or here on this point, at least at the present moment. Please,
                            however, continue to let us have your views in the matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>